=== Etymology ===

According to the ''[[Oxford English Dictionary]]'', ''editor'' comes from the [[Latin language|Latin]] phrase ''e ditus'' which means "to put forward".  The ''editor ludorum'' in [[Ancient Rome]] was the person who put on the games.  In [[French language|French]], ''editeur'' means "publisher".  The word came into [[English language|English]] from French.   The verb ''edit'' is a [[back formation]] from ''editor''.

